{"data":{"names":[{"dateOfBirth":"20 November 1907","placeOfBirth":" Niort, Deux-Sèvres, France","birthName":"Henri Georges Léon Clouzot","bio":"Beginning his film career as a screenwriter, Henri-Georges Clouzot switched over to directing and in 1943 had the distinction of having his film Le corbeau (1943) banned by both the German forces occupying France and the Free French forces fighting them, but for different reasons. He shot to international fame with The Wages of Fear (1953) and consolidated that success with Diabolique (1955), but continuous ill health caused large gaps in his output, and several projects had to be abandoned (though one, L'Enfer (1994), was subsequently filmed by Claude Chabrol). His films are typically relentless suspense thrillers, similar to Alfred Hitchcock's but with far less light relief.","urlPhoto":"https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzQzMjA0OTY5N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjMxNDc3NTE@._V1.jpg","urlIMDB":"http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0167241","name":"Henri-Georges Clouzot","nicknames":["The French Hitchcock"],"idIMDB":"nm0167241","filmographies":[{"section":"Writer","filmography":[{"title":"Diabolique","year":" 1996","remarks":["(screenplay \"Les Diaboliques\")"],"imdbid":"tt0116095"},{"title":"L'Enfer","year":" 1994","remarks":["(1964 script)"],"imdbid":"tt0109731"},{"title":"Woman in Chains","year":" 1968","remarks":["(scenario, adaptation and dialogue)"],"imdbid":"tt0063458"},{"title":"L'enfer","year":" 1964","remarks":null,"imdbid":"tt0058059"},{"title":"The Truth","year":" 1960","remarks":["(scenario)"],"imdbid":"tt0054452"},{"title":"Les espions","year":" 1957","remarks":["(scenario - adaptation, dialogue)"],"imdbid":"tt0050367"},{"title":"If All the Guys in the World...","year":" 1956","remarks":null,"imdbid":"tt0049703"},{"title":"Diabolique","year":" 1955","remarks":["(scenario and dialogue - as H.G. Clouzot)"],"imdbid":"tt0046911"},{"title":"The Wages of Fear","year":" 1953","remarks":["(adaptation and dialogue - as